cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless network design and rate allocation. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses coding-modulation schemes and their impact on transmission rate. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for power control and coding-modulation adaptation. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is another possible category as the algorithm is designed to work in a distributed setting. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but the paper does use simulated annealing to speed up the convergence of the algorithm.
